### 3. Item Spawning / Regeneration

There is **no dedicated runtime item respawning/regeneration script** in this project. Here's what I found regarding spawning:

#### `E:\unity\projs\final_proj\Assets\Editor\BuildMap.cs`

This is an **Editor-only** tool (runs via `Tools > Build 100m Parkour Map` menu) that builds the entire map, including placing:
- Coins (line 364-382)
- Gems (lines 384-392)
- Hearts (lines 391-393)
- Hazards like spikes and saws
- Doors, platforms, decorations, etc.

Items are placed statically at build time — there is no runtime respawning logic.

#### Prefab `Assets/Prefabs/Mg3D_Food/FoodSpawner.prefab`

The name `FoodSpawner.prefab` suggests a spawner exists as a prefab, but **there is no corresponding `FoodSpawner.cs` script** in the `Assets/Scripts/` directory or anywhere else in the project. The prefab likely exists but has no attached spawner behavior script yet (or may use one of the existing scripts like `MoveHorizontal`/`MoveVertical`/`FloatObject` as animation components).

