### Summary of Findings

**1. Player Respawn / Falling Off Map / Boundary Detection:**
- `PlayerController.cs` — Y-boundary check (`deathY = -4f`) triggers `Respawn()`; also handles potion inventory and usage
- `DeathZone.cs` — Trigger zone that calls `Respawn()` on any colliding Player
- `StatusUI.cs` — Triggers `Respawn()` when hunger or sugar hits 0

**2. Item Pickup / Consumable / Collectible Items:**
- `FoodItem.cs` — Trigger-based pickup that adds sugar/hunger to `StatusUI` and self-destructs
- `PotionItem.cs` — Trigger-based pickup that calls `PlayerController.AddPotion()` and self-destructs
- `FoodBaker.cs` (Editor) — Tool to create food prefabs with pre-assigned `FoodItem` stats

**3. Item Spawning / Regeneration:**
- **No runtime spawner/regeneration script exists.** The `BuildMap.cs` editor script places items statically at map build time. A `FoodSpawner.prefab` file exists but has no corresponding spawner behavior script. Item regeneration/re-spawning after collection is not implemented in the current codebase.
